Comment: The experiment was carried out at a Tandem accelerator and the target was a thin film of NaF evaporated onto a thin film of Ag. 
	 The listed uncertainties in the cross-section values are statistical and also due to peak area determination. 
	 There is a systematic uncertainty of 7% (see Sigma scale factor fields). As the gamma detector is placed at an angle close to the neutral angle of 125, 
	 with negligible uncertainty (less than 1%) the total cross section may be obtained by multiplying the given values by 4pi.


